column5: I thought these two bodies of water were all on the same flowage. I spoke with a fellow who is going to stay om Wenesaga and he said the water level is mdeium to high. I have been told that Lac Seul is very low. Confusing to me.

Winnasaga flows into Lac Seul. Mouth of Winnasaga River (on LS) is off limits until like June 1st. That area is know as the walleye santurary. To bad all rivers aren't off limits until the span is over! That will get a few feathers ruffled! Set the hook!

If you fish below the rapids, you can look upstream and you will see about a 6-8 ft drop as the water nears the rapids and falls over the rocks. If the water level of Lac Seul is low, the distance it falls will be even greater. Nice scenery back by the rapids.
that doesn't sound right. lac seul and st joe are at near record lows for this time of year. i think wenasaga lies between them. might be wrong. ????
the wenesaga river empties in to the nw corner of lac-seul. the wenesaga lake has an inlet and outlet which is the wenesaga river. been there twice next week will be 3rd time awesome
Let us know how you did.
